Package: glxosd-data
Multi-arch: foreign
Architecture: all
Depends: libfontconfig1, libfreetype6
Description: Overlay that displays FPS and CPU/GPU temperature in OpenGL applications.
 GLXOSD is an extensible on-screen display (OSD)/overlay for OpenGL applications
 running on Linux with X11 which aims to provide similar functionality to MSI
 Afterburner/RivaTuner OSD. It can show FPS, frame timings, temperatures and
 more in OpenGL games and applications. It can also be used to benchmark games,
 much like voglperf.
 This package provides the scripts and other shared data.

